# Styling Guidelines

The project uses Tailwind CSS with additional utilities:

## Configuration Files
- [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) - Tailwind configuration
- [postcss.config.js](mdc:postcss.config.js) - PostCSS configuration


## UI Specifications
- Use shadcn-ui as the base UI framework.
- The generated UI styles should be aesthetically pleasing.
- Do not use native browser components such as prompt, confirm, or alert.


## Page Specifications
- [utils.ts](mdc:lib/utils.ts) cn function
- [app/login/page.tsx](mdc:app/login/page.tsx) - Login Page
- [app/auth/error/page.tsx](mdc:app/auth/error/page.tsx)- The authentication failure page, where the route parameter will carry error.message.
- [app/stripe/success/page.tsx](mdc:app/stripe/success/page.tsx) - The payment success page
- [app/stripe/cancel/page.tsx](mdc:app/stripe/cancel/page.tsx)- The payment cancellation page.
- [components/UI](mdc:components/UI)- UI component code.
- [components](mdc:components) - Business component code.
- The provider for theme switching is located at providers/theme-provider.tsx
- You are not allowed to modify the code in db/, hooks/, i18n/, lib/, /prisma, or supabase/.